  "texts": [
    "We have predicted in Fig. 2 that DH-SFNNs with multiple branches in each neuron can perform temporal computing tasks via temporal heterogeneity.",
    "In this section, we upgrade the above delayed spiking XOR problem to a multi- timescale spiking XOR problem for testing the model's capability of processing temporally heterogeneous information to further support our prediction.",
    "As depicted in Fig. 4a, the multi-timescale spiking XOR problem uses two types of input spike signals.",
    "At the first stage, a single spike pattern (Signal 1) with a low (left) or high (right) firing rate is fed into the model, representing a low-frequency component.",
    "Then, several similar spike patterns with faster periods (Signal 2) are injected into the model sequentially, representing a high-frequency component."
  ],
